WEBVTT

00:01.958 --> 00:05.327
Ah, Captain.
You're at my desk.

00:05.328 --> 00:07.090
Just what I wanna see
first thing in the morning.

00:07.097 --> 00:08.999
You're three minutes late,
Peralta.

00:09.000 --> 00:11.601
Not my fault.
I had a plumbing problem.

00:11.635 --> 00:12.736
[Musical ringtone]

00:12.737 --> 00:15.246
[Groans]

00:15.247 --> 00:17.249
Which reminds me,
I'm gonna need

00:17.250 --> 00:19.885
a new
departmentally issued phone.

00:19.919 --> 00:21.854
Oh, come on, really?
I'm a few minutes late,

00:21.855 --> 00:23.273
so you're gonna call me out
in front of everyone?

00:23.291 --> 00:25.317
Good idea.
Everyone?

00:25.330 --> 00:28.072
Gather round, so I can call out
Peralta in front of you.

00:28.106 --> 00:31.284
Okay, fine.
I was three minutes late.

00:31.285 --> 00:33.022
I'm sorry for doing
one thing wrong.

00:33.056 --> 00:35.535
- Oh, it's more than one thing.
- Uh-oh.

00:35.559 --> 00:36.661
Let's start
with the Kristov murder.

00:36.662 --> 00:37.965
It was
an amazing solve.

00:37.966 --> 00:39.235
I got him to confess
in 20 minutes.

00:39.236 --> 00:40.672
You also mislabeled
the evidence,

00:40.673 --> 00:42.712
so that confession
is worthless

00:42.746 --> 00:44.485
if the sergeant
hadn't caught your mistake.

00:44.486 --> 00:46.388
Here are three cases
with sloppy paperwork.

00:46.423 --> 00:48.192
Here are two pictures.

00:48.193 --> 00:49.828
One is your locker.

00:49.863 --> 00:52.871
The other is a garbage dump
in the Philippines.

00:52.872 --> 00:57.613
Can you tell
which is which?

00:57.614 --> 01:00.017
- That one's the dump?
- They're both your locker.

01:00.051 --> 01:01.586
Gah, I should've guessed that.
He's good.

01:01.587 --> 01:04.989
This folder is labeled
"undies, dirty."

01:05.024 --> 01:07.025
So I won't confuse it
with "undies, clean."

01:07.060 --> 01:08.862
Also, who cares
about all these rules?

01:08.898 --> 01:11.433
I have more felony arrests
than any other Detective here.

01:11.467 --> 01:14.036
You also have more mice
living in your desk

01:14.037 --> 01:16.038
than any other Detective.

01:16.039 --> 01:18.073
[Gasps] Algernon.
[All aw]

01:18.074 --> 01:20.077
You guys,
Algernon's back.

01:20.111 --> 01:23.314
Get rid of the mouse,
and get your act together now.

01:25.250 --> 01:27.286
He's grumpy.

